[SN]TITLE[SN]
Kenneth Mason named by police as pedestrian killed on East Lothian road

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man who was killed after being hit by a car as he walked along the side of a road in East Lothian has been named by police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Kenneth Mason, 47, from Gullane, was knocked down by a Ford Focus on the A198 at Dirleton, near North Berwick, at 00:10 on Monday.
He was pronounced dead at the scene.
Police said inquiries were ongoing and appealed for witnesses.
